This is a tested track for Chicera Neagra. The climb is steady, no surprises and the entire trail is pretty easy. First, you have to cross the creek on a wooden bridge, then the 1st kilometer is through some gates and near peoples homes (met a few friendly locals). Then the trail continues through the forest and on to the clearing at the top. The actual summit is past the deserted houses and sheds, to the south-east.
